Until java 7 you had to write:<p><pre><code>    List<String> list = new ArrayList<String>();
</code></pre>
It feels silly to have to write the type parameter twice. But now you can say:<p><pre><code>    List<String> list = new ArrayList<>();
</code></pre>
It&#x27;s usually not a <i>huge</i> deal, but occasionally the stutter can be more pronounced:<p><pre><code>    Map<String, List<Map<Integer, Set<Float>>>> map = ...</code></pre>
